reviewText: This film takes you to an earlier time just after WWII. It's gritty, grimy. grainy and depicts the social chaos that was prevelent from then until the 1970's where drug use became rampant, the counterculture was going full swing, and a virtual political and social typhoon of ideas often clashed, particullarly against blacks which are depicted as crows.Although the audio quality is poor and you may have to rewatch and relisten, and the fact that there really is no major plotline, Fritz The Cat used cutting edge animation for the time and it tells a story of a by-gone generation of people through anthropomorphic cartoons.A must have for nostalgia and art decco types!
